snippet.title: Brother of man killed by ex-Dallas cop in his own apartment forgives, embraces her in court
snippet.description:
In a stunning courtroom scene, the brother of Botham Jean, the man killed in his apartment by former Dallas police officer Amber Guyger — who said she mistakenly thought she was in her own apartment and Jean was an intruder — extended forgiveness to her brother's killer, saying he didn't want her to go to jail and wanted the best for her "because that's exactly what Botham would want." 

The 18-year-old Brandt Jean urged Guyger to "give her life to Christ," and, after imploring the judge for permission, walked across the courtroom and embraced her for nearly a full minute.
